"When Mrs. Turner has brought in the tray I will make it clear to you. Now," he said as he turned
hungrily on the simple fare that our landlady had provided, "I must discuss it while I eat, for I
have not much time. It is nearly five now. In two hours we must be on the scene of action. Miss
Irene, or Madame, rather, returns from her drive at seven. We must be at Briony Lodge to meet her."

"And what then?"